With the covid 19 situations in the country where the positivity rate continues to worry about the government. Over the last 24 hours, 1,540 persons tested positive out of a sample size of 9,348, reflecting a positivity rate of 16.5%. the statistics from the ministry of health shows that the capital Nairobi remains with the highest infection rate of 57%. this coming at a time the government says it may institute more stringent measures to contain the spread of the virus especially as the country heads to easter holidays.